@NODE AnimB->GifAnim "AnimB->GifAnim"

@{b}@{u}AnimB->GifAnim@{uu}@{ub}

                  It's a function not binded to the rest of the program:
                  it converts an AnimBrush file (DPaint format) into GifAnim
                  format. By pressing this gadget first will be asked for the
                  name of the source file and then will be asked for the name
                  of the .GIF file that you want to create.








        @{"    Installation   " LINK Installation}
        @{"    Requirements   " LINK Requirements}
        @{"       Usage       " LINK Usage}
        @{"      Commands     " LINK Commands}
        @{"      Effects      " LINK Effects}

        @{"      Author       " LINK Author}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Usage "Usage"

@{b}@{u}USAGE@{uu}@{ub}

The mechanism is very simple:
   you have to select a IFF image,
   you have to select one of the available effects,
   you have to press GO !
After a short lapse of time, it depends on the type of the selected wave
   and the owned processor, you should have in RAM: a file with name
   anim.gif, that is the animation ready to be renamed and used.
Small animations created using DPaint or PPaint may be converted quicky:
   you only need to press the button @{" AnimB --> GifAnim " LINK AnimB->GifAnim}.




